                    <heading>The Environment</heading>
                    <p id="GR.DIR.601">The increase in the number of tourists visiting Greece from the 1960s resulted in construction and industrial activity taking place in many previously undeveloped areas of the country, including numerous islands. The resulting environmental concerns led to an increase in the strength of the environmental movement in Greece. The presÂ­ervation of sites of archaeological interest was another major environmental issue. Comprehensive environmental legislation approved by Parliament on 5 May 2020 attracted some criticism, as it was accused of removing some established elements of environmental protection, particularly in relation to mining, with consultation having been limited owing to the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>
                    <p>In July 2022 a serious wildfire broke out in Dadia National Park, an important protected area.</p>
